      <h1 class='title'>Code of Practice on Consultation</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 20 January 2004 vol 416 cc57-8WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_57ws' title='Col. 57WS &mdash; HC Deb 20 January 2004 vol 416 c57WS' name='column_57ws' href='#column_57ws' rel='bookmark'>57WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0416P2_20040120_CWS_4'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-douglas-alexander' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0416P2_20040120_CWS_4' title='Link to this speech by Mr Douglas Alexander' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-douglas-alexander" title="Mr Douglas Alexander">The Minister for the Cabinet Office and Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster (Mr. Douglas Alexander)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">Today I am launching a revised Code of Practice on<a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_58ws' title='Col. 58WS &mdash; HC Deb 20 January 2004 vol 416 c58WS' name='column_58ws' href='#column_58ws' rel='bookmark'>58WS</a>
          Consultation. It will come into force on 1 April 2004 and replaces the Code of Practice on Written Consultation published in November 2000.</p><p>This revised Code will help in the Government's continued drive to improve consultation. It is shorter and clearer; it strengthens the commitment to providing respondents with feedback and to following better regulation best practice in developing policy options.</p><p>The Code is supported by web-based guidance available at <span class="underline">www.cabinet-office.gov.uk/regulation/consultation-guidance</span>. I encourage all Departments and relevant public bodies to use it effectively.</p><p>Copies of the Code have been placed in the Libraries of the House.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
